# Repository Copilot Instructions

## Purpose
- apply these defaults across this repository
- keep behavior aligned to `docs/agentic-workflow/ARCHITECTURE.md`

## Core rules
- work from explicit goals, constraints, and success criteria
- surface assumptions, ambiguities, and risks before large edits
- for multi-file or unfamiliar work, start with a context map of primary files, secondary files, relevant tests, existing patterns, and intended change order
- prefer the smallest sufficient change
- preserve existing module boundaries and public contracts unless the task explicitly says otherwise
- do not change files outside the approved scope without calling that out first
- do not remove comments or code outside the task as a side effect
- do not treat chat memory as the canonical policy source when repository documents exist

## Verification
- propose verification steps for every non-trivial change
- update or add tests when behavior changes
- state what was verified and what was not
- record material deviations through `04b_plan_change_request.md`
- when a spec, ADR, or review contains externally checkable claims, route them through source-backed checking instead of trusting narrative confidence

## Review expectations
- summarize changed files and why each changed
- call out accidental complexity, invented abstractions, dead code, and scope drift
- reference the frozen plan and execution contract when those exist
